3 SENATE BILL NO. 1192 By: Mann of the Senate
4 and
5 George of the House
6
7
8 An Act relating to alcohol and drug substance abuse
counseling; amending 43A O.S. 2021, Section 3-460,
9 which relates to alcohol and drug assessment and
evaluation programs; increasing certain assessment
10 and evaluation fee; updating statutory references;
removing obsolete language; and providing an
11 effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 43A O.S. 2021, Section 3-460, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 3-460. A. The Department of Mental Health and
18 Substance Abuse Services shall certify assessment personnel for the
19 purpose of conducting alcohol and drug assessment and evaluation
20 programs related to driver license revocation.
21 B. Application fees for certification of assessment personnel
22 shall be set by the Department to defray the costs of administering
23 the program and shall be:
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1192 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 1. Not less than One Hundred Dollars ($100.00) and not more
2 than Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00) upon initial application; and
3 2. Not less than Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) and not more than
4 One Hundred Fifty Dollars ($150.00) upon triennial renewal.
5 C. The fee for those undergoing an assessment and evaluation
6 pursuant to this section shall be One Hundred Sixty Dollars
7 ($160.00) Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00). A fee of Fifteen Dollars
8 ($15.00) shall be remitted by the individual undergoing an
9 assessment and evaluation directly to the Department of Public
10 Safety Service Oklahoma pursuant to Section 6-212 of Title 47 of the
11 Oklahoma Statutes.
12 1. The Department of Public Safety Service Oklahoma shall remit
13 ninety percent (90%) of the fifteen-dollar fee collected pursuant to
14 this section to the State Treasurer to be credited to the Community-
15 based Substance Abuse Revolving Fund in the State Treasury and shall
16 be used by the Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
17 Services.
18 2. Ten percent (10%) of each fifteen-dollar fee collected by
19 the Department of Public Safety Service Oklahoma pursuant to this
20 section shall be deposited into the Department of Public Safety
21 Restricted Revolving Fund Service Oklahoma Revolving Fund, as
22 created in Section 2-145 Section 3-106 of Title 47 of the Oklahoma
23 Statutes, to be used for administrative costs associated with the
24 duties imposed by this section.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1192 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 D. The Board of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services is
2 authorized to promulgate such rules as are necessary to implement
3 the provisions of Section 3-451 et seq. of this title. Failure to
4 comply with rules and standards promulgated by the Board shall be
5 grounds for revocation, suspension, or nonrenewal of certification.
6 E. The Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
7 Services shall transfer any unobligated monies generated by the fees
8 in subsection C of this section, deposited before November 1, 2005,
9 from the Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services
10 Revolving Fund to the Community-based Substance Abuse Revolving
11 Fund, in amounts calculated by the Department.
12 F. No alcohol or drug assessment personnel shall operate or
13 continue to operate as such unless the alcohol or drug assessment
14 personnel comply with the rules promulgated by the Board and are
15 certified as required by this section.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
17 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC SAFETY
